<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-22T16:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-22T16:36:00-05:00" n="1194" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1194">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5317.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-22T15:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1912—3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your October 21, 11 p.m. The most stringent orders were given yesterday
                            and reiterated after Cabinet meeting to-day to do as little <pb facs="0976" n="860" xml:id="pg_860"/> damage as possible to the city
                            of Vera Cruz and especially to foreign interests. There is no intention
                            of bombarding the city; fighting will take place outside of city, fire
                            being directed at barracks.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>